                      4th & Inches Team Construction

The IBM, Tandy Manual

Create America's Team

With the 4th & Inches Team Construction Disk you can modify six existing
teams, or create your own.  You're the ultimate General Manager: choose
the name of your team, and build your roster.  You select your players'
names, stats and skills.  And when you're all through, you can test your
picks on the 4th & Inches gridiron.  So now you're player, coach and owner
- there's no more excuses.

HOW TO GET STARTED

1  Plug in your joystick if you're going to use one.

2  Insert your DOS disk (2.0 or higher for IBM, System DOS for Tandy) into
   Drive A, close the drive door, and switch on your computer.

3  When the A> prompt appears, replace the DOS disk in Drive A with your
   4th & Inches Team Construction Disk, label side up, and close the door.

4  Type Team and press Enter. The game best suited to your system's
   graphics adaptor loads automatically.  (Adaptors include: EGA 16-color,
   CGA or Tandy 4-color, Hercules MGA, and Tandy 16-color)  And the main
   command screen appears.

Main Command Screen (Make Ten Choices)

Use the joystick or keyboard arrows to move the selection bar to any of
these ten options, then press the fire button or Enter to select it.

I/II     Select Visitors / Select Home

Both of these options make six permanent teams appear on screen - the All
Pros, Champs, AccoLads, LacoMites, Angels, and Wildcats - as well as any of
the teams that you create.  To select one, move the selection bar to a team
and press Enter or the fire button.  Your team appears at the top of the
screen in the Visitors or Home column.

				1

                         TEAM CONSTRUCTION

In addition to being able to modify the Disk's six original teams, you can
create your own teams by selecting Blanks.  Blanks appears in the Visitors
or Home column, and now you can create your own team name, names for all
your players, and all stats and skills (for more details see Modify
Visitors / Modify Home.

III/IV  Save Visitors / Save home

After you've created or modified a team, and you're ready to place them on
the field of battle, select this option and press Enter or the fire button.
This saves the team that's displayed in the Visitors of Home slot on the
Main Command screen.  By the way: you don't have to save teams on the Team
Construction Disk.  Any formatted disk will do.  Just replace the Team
Construction Disk with another disk and choose this command.

V/VI    Modify Visitors / Modify Home

You've selected your teams, now you want to change them.  Select either
option to make that team's roster appear on screen.  Whether you're
modifying one of the original sex teams or creating a brand new one, the
changeable information is the same.  Here's a sample:

Team=Angels	Color			QUIT

Position	Name	Height	Weight	  Experience	Attributes

QB1	  Passe, Willie	6'1"	205 lbs.  4th year	Solid
QB2	  Bolle, Bob    6'2"    195 lbs.  2nd year	Quick

To change your team's name: move the selection bar to the Team option and
type in up to eight letters.  But only the first seven will appear on your
4th & Inches playing screen.  By the way: you can't use the six original
names for new teams; the computer won't save them.

To change your jersey color: move the selection bar to the Color option,
then repeatedly press Enter or the fire button to cycle through the 13
different colors.  Whatever background color you choose becomes your jersey
color.  This option, by the way, is available only in the EGA and Tandy
16-color versions of the Team Construction Disk.  In the CGA and

				2

Hercules versions the option doesn't even appear on your screen.

Note:  If two competing teams share the same color, the computer
automatically chooses another one for the Visitors.

To return to the Main Command screen: move the selection bar to QUIT and
press Enter or the fire button.

To switch first and second-string players at every position: move the
selection bar to any position (i.e. QB1) in the position column, the press
Enter or the fire button.  The first-stringer (the one the computer
defaults to) becomes the second, and vice versa.  Press again, and it
changes back to the original order.

To change a player's name: move the selection bar to any name in the name
column (i.e. Passe, Willie), then type the last name first, followed by a
comma, then the first name.  You can create any name up to 13 characters.

To change a player's height and weight: move the selection bar to any row
in the height or weight columns (i.e. 6'2" and 195), then type in new
numbers.  Note: heights must fall between 4'0" and 6'9", weights must fall
between 0 and 399, and only numbers will work.

To change a player's experience: move the selection bar to any row (i.e.
4th year) in the experience column, then type in any combination of letters
or numbers that add up to six.  Examples include: Rookie, Leader, 2nd year.

To select a player's attribute: move the selection bar to any word (i.e.
Quick) in the attribute column, then press Enter or the fire button to
cycle through that player's available skills.  The chart on page 4 tells
you how the different skills affect each position.

