VII     Team Disk Directory

This option displays a list of all of the original and newly-created teams.
Press any key or the fire button to return to the Main Command screen.

VIII    Delete Team

This option also displays a list of all the teams, but now you can erase
them (except for the originals; they can't be erased.)  Select a team, and
press Enter or the fire button.  After the erasure, you automatically
return to the Main Command screen.

IX      Play 4th & Inches

When you choose this option, you are prompted to: "Insert 4th & Inches
diskette; enter any key when ready or ESC to abort."  If you insert the
game disk and press a key, 4th & Inches loads and the game will feature the
Visitors and Home teams that you created. If you press ESC, you exit to
DOS.

Note to Tandy owners: it's a good idea to install your COMMAND.COM file
from your Tandy DOS disk onto your Team Construction Disk.

				4

X       Quit

If you select this option, you exit to DOS, and save whatever modifications
you have made on your Visitors or Home teams.  However, it's a good idea to
use the Save Visitors / Save Home commands to save your handiwork before
you quit.

THE AMIGA MANUAL

Create America's Team

With the 4th & Inches Team Construction Disk you can modify six existing
teams, or create your own.  You're the ultimate General Manager: choose the
name of your team, and build your roster.  You select your players' names,
stats and skills.  And when you're all through, you can test your picks on
the 4th & Inches gridiron.  So now you're player, coach and owner - there's
no more excuses.

How to Get Started

1  Plug in your joystick if you're using one.
2  Kickstart your computer with Kickstart version 1.2 (if necessary)
3  Insert your 4th & Inches Team Construction Disk into the disk drive, 
   label side up.
4  Turn on your computer and the program loads automatically.  After the
   title screen, the Main Command screen appears.

Main Command Screen (Make Ten Choices)

Use the joystick or mouse to move the arrow cursor to any of these ten
options, then press the fire button or left mouse button to select it. 
(Note: to make things less cumbersome, fire button = left mouse button for
the rest of these instructions.)

				5

                 T E A M   C O N S T R U C T I O N

I/II    Select Visitors / Select Home

Both of these options make six permanent teams appear on screen - the All
Pros, Champs, AccoLads, LacoMites, Angels, and Wildcats - as well as any of
the teams that you create.  To select one, move the arrow cursor to a team,
press the fire button to highlight it.

Then move the arrow cursor to the Load Team option and press the fire
button.  The name of your selection appears at the top of the screen in the
Visitors or Home column.

In addition to being able to modify the Disk's six original teams, you can
create your own Visitors or Home teams by selecting the "team" in the list
called -blanks-.  With this selection, you create a name for your team, as
well as all the players' names and statistics (see Modify Visitors / Modify
Home).

To return to the Main Command screen, move the cursor to DONE and press the
fire button.

III/IV   Save Visitors / Save Home

After you've created or modified a team, and you're ready to place them on
the field of battle, select this option and press the fire button.  This
saves the team that's displayed in the Visitors or Home slot on the Main
Command screen.  By the way: you don't have to save teams on your Team
Construction Disk.  Any formatted disk will do - just replace the Team
Construction Disk with another disk and choose this command.

V/VI     Modify Visitors / Modify Home

You've selected your teams, now you want to change them.  Select either
option to make that team's roster appear on screen.  Whether you're
modifying one of the original six teams or creating a brand new one, the
changeable information is the same.  Here's a sample:

Team = Angels             Color               QUIT

Position	Name	   Height	Weight	  Experience   Attributes

QB1	   Passe, Willie    6'1"	205 lbs.   4th year     Solid
QB2        Bolle, Bob       6'2"        195 lbs.   2nd year     Quick

				6

To change your team's name: move the arrow cursor to the name of the team
(i.e. Angels) and press the fire button to highlight it.  Then you can type
in up to eight letters.  But only the first seven will appear on your 4th &
Inches playing screen.  After you type in the name, you must press Return
to enter it.  By the way: you can't use the six original names for new
teams; the computer won't save them.

To change your uniform colors: move the arrow cursor to the Color option,
press the fire button, and the following screen appears.  (Only the mouse
and joystick work on this screen.)

 |------------------------------------------------------------------------|
 |    |------------------------------|                   |-------------|  |
 |    | Shirt Color                  |                   | Team        |  |
 |    |------------------------------|                   |-------------|  |
 |    |------------------------------|                                    |
 |    | Pants Color                  |                                    |
 |    |------------------------------|            |---------------------| |
 |    |------------------------------|            | Flashing Player     | |
 |    | Skin Color                   |            |---------------------| |
 |    |------------------------------|                                    |
 |    |------------------------------|                                    |
 |    | Flash Color                  |                                    |
 |    |------------------------------|                                    |
 |                                                                        |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |    | <                                   > |  | "Red"        |         |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |    | <                                   > |  | "Green"      |         |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |    | <                                   > |  | "Blue"       |         |
 |    |---------------------------------------|  |--------------|         |
 |                                                                        |
