 |                                               | Done                |  |
 |                                               |---------------------|  |
 |------------------------------------------------------------------------|

1  Move the cursor arrow to any of the four color choices - Shirts, Pants,
   Skin, or Flash - then press the fire button to highlight it.

2  Now move the cursor arrow to any of the six arrows on either side of the
   three color bars.

3  Press the fire button repeatedly on a Right arrow to increase the
   intensity of a color; press repeatedly on a Left arrow to decrease it.
   The change is reflected in two places:  first, on the two football
   players (whatever option you "highlight" changes colors), and secondly,
   on the Visitors or Home columns where the team names are listed (the
   background color is the shirt color and the letters are the pants
   color).

				7

4  Use the three color bars to "mix" colors for your highlighted selection.

5  When you choose the Flash Color option, you can select a second set of
   colors for your team.  Both sets will appear on your flashing player -
   the one you control.

6  Move the cursor arrow to DONE and press the fire button to return to the
   Main Command screen.

To return to the Main Command screen: move the arrow cursor to DONE and
press the fire button.

To switch first and second-string player's at every position: move the
arrow cursor to any position (i.e. QB1) in the position column, press the
fire button to highlight it, then press the space bar.  The first-stringer
(the one the computer defaults to) becomes the second, and vice versa. 
Press again, and it changes back to the original order.

To change a player's name: move the arrow cursor to any name in the name
column (i.e. Passe, Willie), press the fire button to highlight it, then
type the last name first, followed by a comma, then the first name.  You
can create any name up to 13 characters.

To change a player's height and weight: move the arrow cursor to any height
or weight in the center two columns (i.e. 6'2" and 195), press the fire
button to highlight it, then type in new numbers.  Note: heights must fall
between 4' 0" and 6' 9", weights must fall between 0 and 399, and only
numbers will work.

To change a player's experience: move the arrow cursor to any row (i.3.,
4th year) in the experience column, press the fire button to highlight it,
then type in any combination of letters of numbers that add up to six. 
Examples include: Rookie, Leader, 2nd year.

To select a player's attribute: move the arrow cursor to any word (i.e.
Quick) in the attribute column, press the fire button to highlight it, then
press the space bar to cycle through the different skills.  See the chart
on page 6 to see how the different skills change the playing style of each
position.

				8

VII     Team Disk Directory

This option displays a list of the original and newly-created teams.  If
you save more teams than can appear on screen at one time, move the arrow
cursor to either arrow icon and press the fire button to scroll through the
list.  Move the arrow cursor to DONE and press the fire button to return to
the Main Command screen.

VIII    Delete Team

This option also displays a list of all the teams, but now you can erase
them (except for the originals; they can't be erased).  Select a team, and
press the fire button to highlight it.  Then move the arrow cursor to
Delete Team and press the fire button - that team is history.  Once again,
move the cursor to DONE and press the fire button to return to the Main
Command screen.

IX      Play 4th & Inches

If you select this option, a prompt appears telling you to "Please insert
volume ACCOLADE Fourth & Inches in any drive."  If you do that, 4th &
Inches loads automatically, and the game will feature the Visitors and Home
teams you created.

X       Quit

If you select this option, you exit to DOS.  Be sure to use the Save
Visitors or Save Home commands before you quit if you want to save any
changes that you've made to your teams.

				9

